# Next.js Frontend

## Project Structure

```
frontend/
├── app/                  # App Router pages and layouts
│   ├── layout.tsx        # Root layout with providers
│   ├── page.tsx          # Landing page (Generate Room)
│   └── [roomId]/
│       └── page.tsx      # Room page (all board states)
├── components/           # Reusable UI components
│   ├── board/            # Board, Column, Note, NoteGroup
│   ├── admin/            # Admin-only: Setup, ActionItems, GroupControls
│   └── ui/               # Shared: Button, Avatar, Timer, ThemeToggle
├── hooks/                # Custom hooks (useWebSocket, useRoom, useTimer)
├── lib/                  # Utilities, API client, WebSocket client
├── stores/               # State management (Zustand)
├── types/                # Shared TypeScript types and enums
└── styles/               # Global CSS variables and theme
```

## Patterns

- Use **Server Components** by default; add `"use client"` only when hooks/interactivity needed.
- State management with **Zustand** — one store per domain concern (room, board, user).
- All types go in `types/` — mirror the backend domain model exactly.
- Use `enum BoardState { SETUP, START, REVIEW, DONE }` to match backend.
- Skeleton notes for guest view: render `<SkeletonNote color={authorColor} />` when user is guest and note is not theirs.

## WebSocket Client

- Connect via SockJS + STOMP to `ws://<backend>/ws`.
- Subscribe to `/topic/room/{roomId}` for broadcasts.
- Send actions to `/app/room/{roomId}/*` destinations.
- Reconnect automatically on disconnect with exponential backoff.

## Component Guidelines

- Props interfaces defined above each component, suffixed with `Props` (e.g. `NoteCardProps`).
- Conditional rendering based on `user.role` (ADMIN vs GUEST) — never duplicate entire pages.
- Drag-and-drop in Review state: use `@dnd-kit/core` for note grouping.
- Timer component receives `endTime` from server and counts down locally.
